{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_58","type":"agent_message","text":"### ISSUE-1: Week locks are enforced only in the UI\n- Category: security\n- Severity: critical\n- Problem: Locked and auto-locked weeks can still be modified by calling the server actions directly. The UI disables cells, but the write paths never verify `attendance_locks` or the \"> 3 days past Monday\" rule.\n- Evidence: [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L112) saves inserts/updates with no lock check; [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L135) does the same; lock enforcement exists only in [attendance-grid.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/components/attendance/attendance-grid.tsx#L175), [office-attendance-grid.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/components/office-attendance/office-attendance-grid.tsx#L117), [attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/attendance/page.tsx#L40), and [office-attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/office-attendance/page.tsx#L31).\n- Suggested fix: In both save actions, derive the affected branch/week server-side, normalize to Monday, and reject writes when a lock row exists or the week is auto-locked. Do not rely on client state for lock enforcement.\n\n### ISSUE-2: Auto-filled `1` statuses are never persisted before lock\n- Category: bug\n- Severity: critical\n- Problem: The grid treats unsaved scheduled/workday cells as `'1'`, but save only sends dirty cells. A user can lock the week with zero dirty changes, leaving the database empty while the UI summary and cron treat the week as complete.\n- Evidence: Default `'1'` is synthesized in [attendance-grid-service.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/services/attendance-grid-service.ts#L127) and [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L104); only dirty cells are saved in [attendance-grid.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/components/attendance/attendance-grid.tsx#L90) and [office-attendance-grid.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/components/office-attendance/office-attendance-grid.tsx#L61); lock is still available in [attendance-grid.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/components/attendance/attendance-grid.tsx#L193); cron uses lock presence as the \"saved\" signal in [route.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/api/cron/weekly-reminder/route.ts#L29).\n- Suggested fix: Either persist all scheduled/workday default `'1'` rows before allowing lock, or keep untouched cells as `null` until an explicit auto-fill/upsert step runs. Cron should validate completeness from attendance rows, not just `attendance_locks`.\n\n### ISSUE-3: Server actions do not validate employee/schedule ownership or assignment\n- Category: security\n- Severity: critical\n- Problem: The server trusts client-supplied `employee_id`, `teacher_id`, `assistant_id`, and `scheduleId`. Because current RLS only checks `branch_id` or `schedule.branch_id`, a branch manager can attach foreign or arbitrary employees to schedules, attendance, office attendance, and weekly notes within their branch.\n- Evidence: Raw IDs are written as-is in [class-schedule-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/class-schedule-actions.ts#L95), [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L128), [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L151), and [weekly-notes-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/weekly-notes-actions.ts#L88); the relevant policies only scope branch/schedule branch in [002_rls_policies.sql](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/supabase/migrations/002_rls_policies.sql#L166), [002_rls_policies.sql](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/supabase/migrations/002_rls_policies.sql#L206), and [002_rls_policies.sql](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/supabase/migrations/002_rls_policies.sql#L261).\n- Suggested fix: Validate referenced entities on the server before every write. Teacher/assistant must be active employees in the effective branch and correct positions; office attendance must target an `office` employee in the same branch; weekly notes must target an employee in the same branch; class attendance must target the schedule’s current teacher/assistant only.\n\n### ISSUE-4: `branchId=\"\"` is handled inconsistently and breaks admin flows\n- Category: bug\n- Severity: high\n- Problem: The stated `branch_id=\"\" => use caller scope` contract is not implemented consistently. Admin pages hardcode `\"\"`, but some actions query `branch_id=''`, some fetch all branches, and create paths try to insert `''` into required UUID fields.\n- Evidence: Empty branch is passed from [attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/attendance/page.tsx#L36), [office-attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/office-attendance/page.tsx#L29), and [class-schedules/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/class-schedules/page.tsx#L81); attendance and office grids hard-filter on that value in [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L60) and [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L56); weekly notes skip the filter when falsy in [weekly-notes-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/weekly-notes-actions.ts#L47); class schedule create uses `data.branch_id` for admin in [class-schedule-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/class-schedule-actions.ts#L89).\n- Suggested fix: Make empty-branch handling uniform. For branch managers, always derive `user.branch_id` on the server. For admins, require an explicit branch id and reject `''`, or add a branch selector and pass a real UUID.\n\n### ISSUE-5: Date keys are timezone-sensitive and can shift backward by one day\n- Category: bug\n- Severity: high\n- Problem: Phase 2 derives attendance dates with `toISOString().split('T')[0]`. In UTC+ time zones, local midnight shifts to the previous UTC date. For example, local Monday March 2, 2026 becomes `2026-03-01`, which breaks week starts, cell keys, locks, and cron checks.\n- Evidence: The root formatter is [date-helpers.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/utils/date-helpers.ts#L38); Phase 2 uses it in [attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/attendance/page.tsx#L34), [office-attendance/page.tsx](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/(dashboard)/office-attendance/page.tsx#L28), [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L53), [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L68), and [route.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/app/api/cron/weekly-reminder/route.ts#L20); grid lookup also does a raw UTC conversion in [attendance-grid-service.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/services/attendance-grid-service.ts#L123).\n- Suggested fix: Stop using UTC ISO serialization for local calendar dates. Build `YYYY-MM-DD` from local year/month/day or use a timezone-safe date library, and normalize incoming week/day values server-side.\n\n### ISSUE-6: Reassigning class staff can orphan historical attendance\n- Category: edge-case\n- Severity: high\n- Problem: Editing `teacher_id` or `assistant_id` on an existing schedule does not reconcile prior attendance rows. After reassignment, old rows remain in `attendance` but disappear from the grid and summary because rendering only uses the current assignees.\n- Evidence: [class-schedule-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/class-schedule-actions.ts#L130) updates schedules without any reconciliation; [attendance-grid-service.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/services/attendance-grid-service.ts#L89) only builds rows for current `teacher_id`/`assistant_id`; the record key includes employee id in [attendance-grid-service.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/services/attendance-grid-service.ts#L83).\n- Suggested fix: Prevent staff reassignment once attendance exists for the affected schedule/week, or migrate/delete old attendance rows transactionally when the assignment changes.\n\n### ISSUE-7: Batch saves are non-idempotent and degrade on larger weeks\n- Category: performance\n- Severity: medium\n- Problem: Inserts use plain `insert`, so concurrent saves race into unique-key errors, and updates are executed one record at a time. That is both slower than necessary and fragile under concurrent use.\n- Evidence: [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L140) bulk-inserts without upsert, then loops updates in [attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/attendance-actions.ts#L145); [office-attendance-actions.ts](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/lib/actions/office-attendance-actions.ts#L161) repeats the same pattern; the DB uniqueness constraints are in [001_create_all_tables.sql](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/supabase/migrations/001_create_all_tables.sql#L133) and [001_create_all_tables.sql](F:/APP%20ANTIGRAVITY/Tool/Luna%20HRM/luna-hrm/supabase/migrations/001_create_all_tables.sql#L154).\n- Suggested fix: Use a single upsert path keyed on `(schedule_id, employee_id, date)` for class attendance and `(employee_id, date)` for office attendance, and replace per-row updates with one batched statement or RPC.\n\n### VERDICT\n- Status: REVISE\n- Reason: Core controls are not enforced server-side, default attendance can be locked without ever being written, and several write paths trust client-provided relationships that are not validated against branch or assignment rules."}}
